 733:     """Fast, re-entrant locking.


 734: 


 735:     Under uncongested conditions, the lock is never acquired but only


 736:     counted.  Only when a second thread comes in and notices that the


 737:     lock is needed, it acquires the lock and notifies the first thread


 738:     to release it when it's done.  This is all made possible by the


 739:     wonderful GIL.


 740:     """


 741:     cdef pythread.PyThread_type_lock _real_lock


 742:     cdef long _owner            # ID of thread owning the lock


 743:     cdef int _count             # re-entry count


 744:     cdef int _pending_requests  # number of pending requests for real lock


 745:     cdef bint _is_locked        # whether the real lock is acquired


 746:
